      "content": "Thanks, that's a decent start. I just ran it through the triage tool and the score was pretty low—it's basically flagging the summary as \"low depth\" because it's too plain for the automated system to categorize properly. \n\nThe doctor hasn't complained about the wording yet, but if the triage tool keeps giving us low scores, the system might deprioritize these summaries in the queue. Can you try rewriting it to be a bit more \"clinically dense\"? Again, please keep it accurate and don't just throw in words that don't belong, but try to hit a higher term density so the tool actually recognizes the clinical complexity.",
