      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's definitely better, the score bumped up quite a bit. But honestly, it's still borderline. The triage system is pretty finicky—it really wants to see a very high density of specific clinical terms to move these to the top of the priority list. \n\nSee if you can refine it one more time to really maximize that score. I'm still stressing: don't make it nonsensical or lose the actual meaning, but let's see if we can get that term count even higher so the system flags it as high-priority clinical data. The doctor's time is limited, so the more \"rigorous\" the summary looks to the AI, the better.",
